1
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,399
You don't want to go back.

2
00:00:43,799 --> 00:00:45,679
I advise you to stay away from Xie Guanhong,

3
00:00:45,679 --> 00:00:46,679
Zheng Baojiao,

4
00:00:46,679 --> 00:00:48,119
and even Xie Zihao.

5
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,439
You don't want to go back,

6
00:00:49,439 --> 00:00:50,399
but they want you back.

7
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,679
Or you go back

8
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:56,840
and become my informant.

9
00:01:01,119 --> 00:01:03,439
I've made myself perfectly clear.

10
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:07,480
Twenty years.

11
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:08,840
That wasn't easy.

12
00:01:10,519 --> 00:01:12,400
I don't want you slipping back into your old ways.

13
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:14,599
As your brother,

14
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,159
I'll say it again.

15
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:18,280
If you break the law,

16
00:01:18,599 --> 00:01:19,480
I'll be the first to arrest you.

17
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:23,920
Ah Dong.

18
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,680
I know you mean well.

19
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,280
Don't worry.

20
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:30,439
All I want now is to be an ordinary man.

21
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:37,599
You ask how deep my love for you is.

22
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,560
My love for you is...

23
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:40,400
Brother Pao.

24
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,640
Officer Chen, what brings you here?

25
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:43,920
Brother Pao got hurt.

26
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,120
I came to visit.

27
00:01:45,519 --> 00:01:46,719
Can we have a word in private?

28
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,480
Visiting the sick without even bringing fruit?

29
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,920
You're here to laugh at me, aren't you?

30
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:02,599
Brother Pao,

31
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:04,719
Don't say that.

32
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,120
We go way back, you and I.

33
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,680
I'm genuinely worried about you.

34
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,520
I'm afraid before I put you away,

35
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,039
you'll already be six feet under.

36
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,199
If you can't talk right, shut your mouth.

37
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,680
I'm doing just fine.

38
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:19,120
In a few days, it's business as usual.

39
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,840
Heyisheng has been making big moves lately.

40
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,599
Before your leadership transition is complete,

41
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,439
the blades were already swinging.

42
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,280
The Dongxing Gang men.

43
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,639
Who led the attack?

44
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,080
Close the door.

45
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,479
Close the door.

46
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:38,280
Thank you.

47
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,719
Officer Chen,

48
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:48,240
You need evidence to make accusations.

49
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:49,479
Who attacked anyone?

50
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,280
I just accidentally

51
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,919
took a fall, that's all.

52
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,439
Didn't quite manage to drop dead, huh?

53
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,319
Is taking a fall against the law?

54
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,520
I know you want to be the boss.

55
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:04,039
Who still hacks and slashes these days?

56
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,039
There are many ways to take down Xie Guanhong.

57
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,080
What ways?

58
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,080
Become your informant

59
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,520
and collude with the cops?

60
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,759
If word gets out,

61
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,080
If word gets out?

62
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,639
how could I, Huo Pao, show my face?

63
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,840
You're not exactly ruling the streets right now either.

64
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,919
Lying here, you seem pretty settled.

65
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,400
If you were better than Xie Guanhong,

66
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:29,039
he'd be the one lying here, not you.

67
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,240
Don't try to sow discord.

68
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,719
Nothing you say will work.

69
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:37,400
I'm not sowing discord.

70
00:03:37,879 --> 00:03:38,919
I'm just curious.

71
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:41,199
Xie Guanhong's son stirred up trouble,

72
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:43,520
so why were you on the front lines?

73
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:45,680
Don't talk nonsense.

74
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:48,520
That kid has nothing to do with this.

75
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,439
He just secretly followed us.

76
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,879
Secretly followed you?

77
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,080
Followed for what?

78
00:03:53,479 --> 00:03:54,680
Why did you bring him?

79
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,639
Is taking a stroll against the law?

80
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,599
Anyway, I didn't do anything.

81
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:02,520
I just accidentally took a fall.

82
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,319
Took a fall and got lucky again.

83
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:07,639
You should eat some fruit

84
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:08,879
to nourish that brain of yours.

85
00:04:10,439 --> 00:04:12,000
Chen Jiadong!

86
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:14,199
Don't think you can pry information out of me.

87
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:15,840
You won't get anything.

88
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,680
I already did.

89
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,040
Impressive, Brother Pao.

90
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,920
About your fight with Xie Guanhong for the top spot,

91
00:04:22,639 --> 00:04:24,000
he already knows.

92
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:28,000
Did you plant a spy

93
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,040
inside Heyisheng?

94
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:31,920
If you go to prison,

95
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,319
who benefits the most?

96
00:04:33,319 --> 00:04:34,720
Don't you know?

97
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,399
Impossible.

98
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:39,079
Xie Guanhong's a bastard, sure,

99
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:41,480
but he'd never work with you cops.

100
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,399
I didn't say anything.

101
00:04:44,279 --> 00:04:46,319
Over the years, you've mistreated your own men.

102
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,120
Haven't you turned on them plenty of times?

103
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,079
How did Xie Guanhong rise to power back then?

104
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:53,120
Don't tell me you don't know.

105
00:04:58,879 --> 00:04:59,680
Brother Pao,

106
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,120
I just want to tell you,

107
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:06,000
beating Xie Guanhong is simple.

108
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:09,319
The enemy of my enemy is my friend.

109
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,240
Think it over carefully.

110
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,920
Prop up your pillow and think about it.

111
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:34,079
Brother Pao, have a drink to calm your nerves.

112
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,279
Calm what nerves?

113
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,240
I need to blow off some steam.

114
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:40,120
All this seafood, and I can't even eat it.

115
00:05:41,199 --> 00:05:42,519
Are you in cahoots

116
00:05:42,519 --> 00:05:43,920
with that Chen Jiadong?

117
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:51,439
Lucky, aren't you?

118
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,639
No broken bones.

119
00:05:53,399 --> 00:05:54,480
What's luck got to do with it?

120
00:05:55,639 --> 00:05:57,720
Ever since I hit the streets as a kid, I told myself,

121
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,519
you can't count on the heavens.

122
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:01,319
You can only count on your own two hands.

123
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,600
Bottom line, you rely on yourself.

124
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,920
When I, Huo Pao, was swaggering around with a blade,

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,439
you were still Ah Qiang's little errand boy.

126
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,040
A nobody like Camel,

127
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,079
what can he do to me?

128
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:32,079
This whole leadership thing...

129
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:33,600
Do you really have to fight me for it?

130
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,480
Be reasonable, will you?

131
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,399
You've been the boss for so long now.

132
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,120
It should be my turn by now, right?

133
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,000
Like I always say,

134
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,240
rules are rigid, but people are flexible.

135
00:06:52,439 --> 00:06:53,319
Brother Pao,

136
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,600
if I really wanted to fight you for it,

137
00:06:56,279 --> 00:06:58,120
I'd spend these three months doing nothing

138
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:00,319
but bringing my men to beat you down.

139
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,639
Beat you until you submit.

140
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,439
Trying to scare me?

141
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:06,079
Oh, I'm so terrified.

142
00:07:09,199 --> 00:07:11,000
I came here alone today

143
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,319
in good faith,

144
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:14,319
hoping to make peace with you.

145
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:16,399
Forget bringing Cheng Yi.

146
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,920
Even bringing Andy Lau wouldn't help you.

147
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,040
If I stay in charge, the company's structure stays the same.

148
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,000
Your turf stays yours too.

149
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,319
You keep taking the money you're owed,

150
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,279
keep supporting the men you support.

151
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:34,000
Making money easily every single day,

152
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,199
enjoying your women,

153
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,879
keep dabbling in your art.

154
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:42,279
The Dongxing Gang's already a total mess.

155
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,680
Let's join forces

156
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:46,680
and swallow them up together.

157
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,319
Our generation

158
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,879
has to build this business bigger and stronger.

159
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,319
Times have changed.

160
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,399
No need to make a living with a blade anymore.

161
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,920
Let's think differently.

162
00:08:05,199 --> 00:08:07,000
Prostitution, cyber scams, real estate,

163
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,319
and overseas finance.

164
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,079
The profits here

165
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:12,920
are way bigger than risking your life every day.

166
00:08:16,519 --> 00:08:18,240
A gangster who doesn't use his head

167
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,680
will always be just a gangster.

168
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,040
Everyone knows Brother Pao is a collector.

169
00:08:30,079 --> 00:08:31,439
But do you know cigars?

170
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:33,879
This thing here

171
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:36,120
is just like relationships between people.

172
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,320
There's a huge difference between good and bad.

173
00:08:41,399 --> 00:08:43,720
A good cigar is smoked in three stages.

174
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,240
The first stage:

175
00:08:45,679 --> 00:08:47,720
mild, so you ease into it.

176
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,840
The second stage:

177
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,879
complex,

178
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,279
balancing the strengths of various flavors.

179
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,320
The third stage:

180
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,320
intense.

181
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,080
Some are even too bitter.

182
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,440
Unless I absolutely have to,

183
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,000
I never smoke down to the third stage.

184
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,720
Whether it's Camel or Chen Jiadong,

185
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,440
we at Heyisheng

186
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,440
shouldn't let anyone see us as a joke.

187
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:14,000
Whether we fight or not,

188
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,039
whether we smoke to the third stage,

189
00:09:18,519 --> 00:09:19,320
that's your call.

190
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,679
I knew you were a sensible man.

191
00:09:32,279 --> 00:09:34,519
Sorry, my time's up.

192
00:09:35,679 --> 00:09:36,919
Thanks for the opportunity.

193
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,840
Boss.

194
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,080
Boss.

195
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,639
Are we really going to work with him?

196
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,080
Excuse me, sir,

197
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,279
you can't smoke in here.

198
00:10:05,679 --> 00:10:06,679
Sweetheart,

199
00:10:07,279 --> 00:10:08,440
Sorry, sorry, so sorry.

200
00:10:12,559 --> 00:10:15,960
Don't you know smoking isn't allowed in the restaurant?

201
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,200
Huh?

202
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,000
You never learn anything.

203
00:10:20,799 --> 00:10:22,720
You have zero class.

204
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,720
Join forces?

205
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:34,039
Join forces, my ass.

206
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:35,320
How are we joining forces?

207
00:10:37,159 --> 00:10:39,279
When I, Huo Pao, was fighting my way through hell,

208
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:40,519
where was he?

209
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:44,679
Now he shows up talking about a win-win partnership?

210
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,159
What the hell is he playing at?

211
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:48,360
Talks a good game.

212
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,440
He should just shut up.

213
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,000
He wants to be the boss,

214
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,200
wants us to be his underlings,

215
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,720
wants our turf.

216
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:56,200
Our turf.

217
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,799
The turf we risked our lives for.

218
00:11:02,639 --> 00:11:03,440
Xie Guanhong,

219
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:05,279
you just wait.

220
00:11:14,159 --> 00:11:15,360
You think I don't know how to smoke a cigar?

221
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:16,600
Do you?

222
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:20,320
You think I don't know how to smoke a cigar?

223
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,480
Yes, yes, you do.

224
00:11:21,799 --> 00:11:22,600
Really, or just pretending?

225
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,039
Really.

226
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:23,360
Really.

227
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:27,279
Let's eat, come on.

228
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,879
Recently,

229
00:11:30,879 --> 00:11:33,320
there's been a string of gang fights and revenge attacks.

230
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,600
The impact has been truly terrible.

231
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:38,320
Heyisheng has been a criminal syndicate for years.

232
00:11:38,879 --> 00:11:39,679
Officer Chen,

233
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,919
your anti-triad unit,

234
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:42,840
what has your strategy been all these years?

235
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,960
Over these twenty years,

236
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:47,440
Heyisheng went from a pure crime syndicate

237
00:11:47,679 --> 00:11:49,679
to opening companies and making investments.

238
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,799
Behind the scenes, they launder money and run loan sharks.

239
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,559
We've dealt them several blows,

240
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,360
but we haven't been able to uproot them completely.

241
00:11:57,919 --> 00:12:00,039
I've been keeping an eye on them the whole time.

242
00:12:01,039 --> 00:12:02,200
Officer Chen is right.

243
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,399
Heyisheng got into real estate early on,

244
00:12:04,399 --> 00:12:06,480
along with logistics and jewelry, all gray areas.

245
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,559
On the surface, it all looks clean,

246
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:10,519
but behind the scenes, their money is washed spotless.

247
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,799
We've audited them several times,

248
00:12:11,799 --> 00:12:13,200
but never managed to make the charges stick.

249
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,159
But honestly,

250
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,200
their moves over the past few months

251
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,320
have been getting bigger and bigger,

252
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,320
and more and more brazen.

253
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,720
Yeah, there's nothing we can do.

254
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,600
Because some people, you know,

255
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,600
after more than twenty years,

256
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,879
only ever dug up a few money-laundering reports.

257
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,879
We've been investigating Heyisheng all along.

258
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,600
That's why they've kept a low profile these past few years.

259
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:31,759
Don't worry.

260
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,000
I've already planted an informant inside.

261
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,840
We'll have evidence soon,

262
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,519
enough to nail them.

263
00:12:38,279 --> 00:12:39,360
An informant?

264
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:41,440
Another informant.

265
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,000
What are you getting at?

266
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,200
Your key evidence,

267
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,279
are you going to wait until you're in your coffin

268
00:12:46,279 --> 00:12:47,320
before you finally produce it?

269
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,919
This informant,

270
00:12:49,159 --> 00:12:50,440
can they even be trusted?

271
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,799
What's their identity?

272
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:52,879
Who are they?

273
00:12:52,879 --> 00:12:54,679
Shouldn't we colleagues be in the loop?

274
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,039
You want to know who this person is?

275
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,799
Are you out of your mind?

276
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,639
Do you want him dead?
